header.gameNote: DUEL IN THE DESERT AT LAS VEGAS NV

article.headline: South Florida 87, Norfolk State 56
article.story: LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Kentrell Gransberry had a game-high 24 points and 11 rebounds and Jesus Verdejo added 20 points as the University of South Florida men's basketball team beat Norfolk State 87-56 Sunday night in the opening game of the Duel In The Desert, hosted by University of Nevada at Las Vegas. Norfolk State (1-6) scored the first points of the game, but USF's Melvin Buckley hit a 3-pointer giving his team the lead the rest of the way. Verdejo's three-pointer with 9:38 to play in the first half capped a 19-6 run and gave the Bulls (7-1) a 24-11 advantage. Gransberry and Verdejo, midyear transfers last season, were both making their respective USF debuts. Calvin Brown had a team-high 23 points for the Spartans and Corey Lyons added nine. South Florida's Melvin Buckley added 15 points and Solomon Bozeman added 13 points.
